Package: lpt
Type: Package
Title: Local Parallel Trends for Continuous Difference-in-Differences
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: person("Francesco", "Dealberti", email = "dealberti.francesco@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Implements partial identification for continuous
    difference-in-differences designs under local restrictions on
    counterfactual trends. A level bound M on trend deviations
    (|mu_t(d) - mu_t(0)| <= M) yields identified sets for ATT levels and
    the overall ATT; a separate slope bound B on selection slopes
    (|mu_t'(d)| <= B) yields identified sets for dose-response
    derivatives. Identified sets widen linearly in the post-treatment
    horizon, and both bounds can be calibrated from pre-treatment
    periods. Estimation uses penalized regression splines via mgcv, with
    contdid, npiv, and kernel backends. See Dealberti (2026) for details.
